                            <comment id="17068080" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2020 21:53:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cadonna commented on pull request #8368: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9770&quot; title=&quot;Caching State Store does not Close Underlying State Store When Exception is Thrown During Flushing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-9770&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-9770&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Close underlying state store also when flush throws&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/8368&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/8368&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   When a caching state store is closed it calls its flush() method.&lt;br/&gt;
   If flush() throws an exception the underlying state store is not closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   This commit ensures that state stores underlying a caching state store&lt;br/&gt;
   are closed even when flush() throws.&lt;/p&gt;

